TEXT(beginproblem());

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the system of equations
\[
\begin{array}{rcrccl}
3x&+&2y&=&17\\
x&-&y&=&-1\\
\end{array}
\]
Its solution is
$BR
\(x=\)\{ ans_rule(6) \} and
EOT
ANS(num_cmp("3"));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
\(y=\)\{ ans_rule(6) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp("4"));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT'));
EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
Proceeding as
\{htmlLink("http://www.math.utah.edu/online/1010/lisys/",
"described here")\}  obtain the table:

\[
\begin{array}{lrrrr}
\hbox{equation}&x&y&\hbox{RHS}&\hbox{RS}\\ \\
{[1]}&3&2&17&22\\
{[2]}&1&-1&-1&-1\\
{[3]=[1]+2[2]}&5&0&15&20\\
\end{array}
\]
The last row of this table means that \(5x=15\) or \(x=3\).
Substituting \(x\) in the second equation gives \(y=4\). 
EOT





